noria:TroubleTicket/TT-20240423-005 noria:troubleTicketTrigger noria:EventRecord/Log-EmailServerCrash .

# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All entities have rdf:type, rdfs:label, rdfs:comment/skos:example.
# - All entities are linked to at least one other entity via NORIA properties.
# - A good mix of classes and properties are used.
# - Kos concepts are defined and used.
# - No ldp prefix.
# - Logical blocks are used.

# The graph is quite dense now, with multiple layers of relationships:
# Agents manage Resources and Applications.
# Resources are located at Loci within Rooms within Sites.
# Resources have ProductModels.
# Resources have NetworkInterfaces.
# NetworkInterfaces connect to NetworkLinks.
# Resources support Applications.
# Applications have ApplicationModules.
# ApplicationModules are managed by Agents/Teams.
# Services are composed of Applications/ApplicationModules/Resources.
# EventRecords originate from Resources/Applications/Agents.
# TroubleTickets are triggered by EventRecords, relate to Services/Applications/Resources/Agents, and have Notes.
# ChangeRequests impact Services/Applications/Resources/Agents.
# OperationPlans have Pre/Post Conditions and are correlated with actions in TroubleTickets/ChangeRequests.
# DocumentAttachments are part of TroubleTickets.

# This structure ensures high connectivity and density, reflecting a complex IT environment.
